examples.en: I'm sure his motives were worthy.
As far as we can judge, motives and actions do strictly correspond to each other.
I fail to understand your motives.
We only conjecture about his motives.
Were his motives entirely altruistic?
What motives could they impute to him?
I have my suspicions about his motives.
I began to suspect his motives in inviting me.
I suspected his motives in giving me the money.
The motives behind the decision remain obscure.
Her motives have been scrutinized and impugned.
I really had no operative motives for doing it.
She could only speculate about her friend's motives.
The character's motives remain accidental to the plot.
The violence was clearly prompted by political motives.
Varied motives prompt people to join a political party.
His motives in choosing a career were purely mercenary.
I suspected that his motives for helping us were questionable.
She has a natural ability to understand the motives of others.
She denied that her offer to help was based on selfish motives.
He's just being nice. I don't think he has any ulterior motives.
I think you should examine their motives in offering to lend you the money.
The success of their labours was answerable to the purity of their motives.
The archbishop was aware of the motives by which the papal decisions were governed.
His motives for volunteering lie somewhere on the continuum between charitable and self-serving.
